@node Main "Aye_Q - Documentation"

                              'Aye_Q' 1.24

                           by Charles-N. Jacob

  'Aye_Q' is a @{" Workbench game " link play} like 'Solo' or 'Hi-Q'. You play by
jumping a peg to an empty space either horizontally or vertically,
and depending if you play the @{"Normal" link play} or @{"Inverted" link play} game, that peg
must go over another peg (or empty space in the Inverted game). In
the @{"Normal" link play} game, the intermediate peg (the one that was jumped
over) will be removed. In the @{"Inverted" link play} game, the intermediate
empty space will be replaced by a peg.

  The goal is to remove all the pegs, leaving only one on the
board. If you play the @{"Inverted" link play} game, you start with one peg and
you try to fill the board leaving only one empty space.

  Have fun!

               @{" Install and Play the game " link play}
               @{"   Features of the game    " link features}
               @{"          History          " link histo}
               @{"        Legal stuff        " link legal}
               @{"          Credits          " link credits}

